One-Year O/E Graft Survival v.s. Diabetes Proportions

Fan Wu

April 5, 2016

We merge the OPTN/UNOS data with the annual report from the SRTR website. We extract three diabetes proportions (p.diab = total; p.diab1 = diabetes I; p.diab2 = diabetes II). We plot the scatter plots and fitted the Observed/Expected one-year graft survival for all centers with O/E greater than .85 and total proportion of diabetes greater than 20%. Linear regressions are fitted (plotted as the straight line in each panel).

We plot the scatter-plot matrix for the diabetes proportions and the 1-year O/E graft survival.

The scatter plots with smoother are shown below.

Simple linear regressions are fitted for each diabetes proportions (in \(\log_{10}\) scale), adjusted for center size (number of TXs). All diabetes slope estimates are small and not significant.
